1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 321, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 321. The A. Except as provided in subsection B of this
4 section, the following sales are hereby exempted from the stamp
5 excise tax levied pursuant to the provisions of Section 301 et seq.
6 of this title:
7 1. All cigarettes sold to veterans hospitals and state operated
8 domiciliary homes for veterans located in the State of Oklahoma, for
9 distribution or sale to disabled ex-servicemen or disabled ex-
10 servicewomen interned in, or inmates of, such hospitals, or
11 residents of such homes;
12 2. All sales to the United States;
13 3. All sales to a federally recognized Indian tribe or nation
14 which has entered into a compact with the State of Oklahoma pursuant
15 to the provisions of subsection C of Section 1 of this act or to a
16 licensee of such a tribe or nation, upon which the payment in lieu
17 of taxes required by the compact has been paid; and
18 4. All sales to a federally recognized Indian tribe or nation
19 or to a licensee of such a tribe or nation upon which the tax levied
20 pursuant to the provisions of Section 4 of this act has been paid.
21 B. To the sale of cigarettes that are intended to be heated
22 rather than burned shall be applied a tax exemption equal to fifty
23 percent (50%) of the tax levied pursuant to subsection A of this
24 section.
Req. No. 10892 Page 7
1 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 322, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 322. The Oklahoma Tax Commission shall prescribe such
4 rules and make such regulations as to the sale or distribution of
5 cigarettes, and the exemption from the stamp excise tax thereof, as
6 shall be deemed necessary to comply with the provisions of the
7 preceding section Section 301 et seq of this title, including the
8 creation of distinct stamps to affix to packages of cigarettes that
9 are intended to be heated rather than burned, and provide that such
10 stamps be made available on or before the effective date of this
11 act.
12 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
